# QA Skills Ecosystem

## Project Overview
This is a QA automation skills ecosystem for Cursor IDE. It contains 45+ specialized agent skills covering the full QA lifecycle: documentation, test case design, test writing (TypeScript + Python + specialized), reporting, analysis, and orchestration.

## Architecture
- Skills live in `.cursor/skills/qa-{name}/SKILL.md`
- Rules live in `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`
- MCP servers configured in `.cursor/mcp.json`
- API keys stored in `.env` (never hardcode)
- Templates in `templates/`
- Memory bank in `memory-bank/`

## Skill Quality Standards
Every skill MUST include:
1. YAML frontmatter with `name` and `description`
2. Decision autonomy levels (can do / cannot do / will not do)
3. Quality checklist before each deliverable
4. Troubleshooting table (Symptom | Cause | Fix)
5. Progressive loading (SKILL.md < 500 lines, details in references/)

## Naming Conventions
- Skills: `qa-{purpose}` (lowercase, hyphens)
- Rules: `qa-{domain}.mdc`
- References: `references/{topic}.md`

## Key Patterns
- Diagram generator is embeddable -- other skills reference its patterns
- Task creator works standalone AND paired with bug-ticket-creator
- Playwright writers support record mode (live browser generation)
- Test healer auto-fixes broken selectors/assertions

## Languages & Frameworks
- TypeScript: Jest, Vitest, Playwright, Cypress, WebdriverIO, CodeceptJS, Supertest
- Python: pytest, Playwright, Selenium, Robot Framework, httpx
- Cross-language: k6, Locust, JMeter, OWASP ZAP, axe-core, Pact, Appium

## Standards
- ISO/IEC/IEEE 29148 (requirements)
- ISO/IEC/IEEE 29119-3/4 (test documentation & techniques)
- ISO/IEC 25010 (quality model)
- WCAG 2.2 (accessibility)
- OWASP WSTG (security testing)
